Step 1: Identify the needed values from the problem.
• Net Profit = 1,105,265.77 
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 803,237.11

Step 2: Use the formula for Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio:
  Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Net Profit)

Step 3: Compute the ratio:
  Ratio = 803,237.11 / 1,105,265.77 ≈ 0.7267

Step 4: Rounding the ratio to two decimal places gives approximately 0.73.

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is 0.73.
